018package org.tquadrat.bloodpressure;
019
020import static org.apiguardian.api.API.Status.STABLE;
021
022import org.apiguardian.api.API;
023import org.tquadrat.foundation.annotation.ClassVersion;
024
025/**
026 *  <p>{@summary An instance of
027 *  {@code DataNode}
028 *  holds only the systolic and diastolic pressures as integer values, based on
029 *  mmHG, but not the timestamp.}</p>
030 *  <p>It is used for the inputs to the reports.</p>
031 *
032 *  @param  systolic    The systolic pressure in mmHG.
033 *  @param  diastolic   The diastolic pressure in mmHG.
034 *  @param  pulsePressure   This is the difference between the systolic and the
035 *      diastolic pressure.
036 *
037 *  @version $Id: DataNode.java 119 2022-02-10 18:55:45Z tquadrat $
038 *  @extauthor Thomas Thrien - thomas.thrien@tquadrat.org
039 *  @UMLGraph.link
040 *  @since 0.0.1
041 */
042@ClassVersion( sourceVersion = "$Id: DataNode.java 119 2022-02-10 18:55:45Z tquadrat $" )
043@API( status = STABLE, since = "0.0.1" )
044public record DataNode( int systolic, int diastolic, int pulsePressure )
045{
046        /*--------------*\
047    ====** Constructors **=====================================================
048        \*--------------*/
049    /**
050     *  Creates a new instance of {@code DataNode}. The {@code pulsePressure}
051     *  will be calculated.
052     *
053     *  @param  systolic    The systolic pressure in mmHG.
054     *  @param  diastolic   The diastolic pressure in mmHG.
055     */
056    public DataNode( final int systolic, final int diastolic )
057    {
058        this( systolic, diastolic, systolic - diastolic );
059    }   //  DataNode()
060}
061//  record DataNode
062
063/*
064 *  End of File
065 */
